<p><i><b>A Deepness in the Sky</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> <a href="/wiki/Novel" title="Novel">novel</a> by <a href="/wiki/Vernor_Vinge" title="Vernor Vinge">Vernor Vinge</a>. Published in 1999, the novel is a loose <a href="/wiki/Prequel" title="Prequel">prequel</a> (set twenty thousand years earlier) to his earlier novel <i><a href="/wiki/A_Fire_Upon_the_Deep" title="A Fire Upon the Deep">A Fire Upon the Deep</a></i> (1992). The title is coined by one of the main characters in a debate, in a reference to the hibernating habits of his species and to the vastness of space.</p>
